  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1535183335" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1535183335" />
    <a title="Margaret" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3717253-margaret"><img alt="Margaret" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1332605246p2/3717253.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1535183335?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Margaret" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Margaret" href="/user/show/3717253-margaret">Margaret</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1535183335" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer815090150427032811">This is a lovely little story, really a meditation on life and what it means to be alive... while dying. I &quot;read&quot; it as an audiobook and expect I&apos;ll read it again one day, with the referenced paintings in front of me. (I believe they are printed in the book.) It made me appreciate Mary Cassatt&apos;s paintings more than I had. </span>
  <span id="freeText815090150427032811" style="display:none">This is a lovely little story, really a meditation on life and what it means to be alive... while dying. I "read" it as an audiobook and expect I'll read it again one day, with the referenced paintings in front of me. (I believe they are printed in the book.) It made me appreciate Mary Cassatt's paintings more than I had. </span>
  <a data-text-id="815090150427032811" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


